vel-frameset-carbon-1-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03074832/allied-cycle-works-echo-all-road-bike-gravel-frameset-carbon-1-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03074832/allied-cycle-works-echo-all-road-bike-gravel-frameset-carbon-1-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03074832/allied-cycle-works-echo-all-road-bike-gravel-frameset-carbon-1-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03074832/allied-cycle-works-echo-all-road-bike-gravel-frameset-carbon-1-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a>When we think of All-Road bikes, we tend to think of a road bike frame that simply has above average tire clearance. You simply swap out your slick tires for some higher volume knobbly ones and boom, you’re ready for a gravel adventure. The Allied Cycle Works Echo is no ordinary All-Road bike, however.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03075018/allied-cycle-works-echo-dropout-flip-chip-geometry-adjustment.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03075018/allied-cycle-works-echo-dropout-flip-chip-geometry-adjustment.jpg\" alt=\"allied cycle works echo flip chip chainstay length adjust\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03075018/allied-cycle-works-echo-dropout-flip-chip-geometry-adjustment.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03075018/allied-cycle-works-echo-dropout-flip-chip-geometry-adjustment-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2