247/allied-cycle-works-echo-all-road-gravel-bike-tire-clearance-40mm-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03075247/allied-cycle-works-echo-all-road-gravel-bike-tire-clearance-40mm-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03075247/allied-cycle-works-echo-all-road-gravel-bike-tire-clearance-40mm-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03075247/allied-cycle-works-echo-all-road-gravel-bike-tire-clearance-40mm-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03075247/allied-cycle-works-echo-all-road-gravel-bike-tire-clearance-40mm-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03075247/allied-cycle-works-echo-all-road-gravel-bike-tire-clearance-40mm-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03075247/allied-cycle-works-echo-all-road-gravel-bike-tire-clearance-40mm.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03075247/allied-cycle-works-echo-all-road-gravel-bike-tire-clearance-40mm.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03075247/allied-cycle-works-echo-all-road-gravel-bike-tire-clearance-40mm-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03075247/allied-cycle-works-echo-all-road-gravel-bike-tire-clearance-40mm-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03075247/allied-cycle-works-echo-all-road-gravel-bike-tire-clearance-40mm-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03075247/allied-cycle-works-echo-all-road-gravel-bike-tire-clearance-40mm-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03075247/allied-cycle-works-echo-all-road-gravel-bike-tire-clearance-40mm-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03075247/allied-cycle-works-echo-all-road-gravel-bike-tire-clearance-40mm-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03075247/allied-cycle-works-echo-all-road-gravel-bike-tire-clearance-40mm-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-medrectangle-3\"></span></p><p>With the chips flipped, the gravel geometry gives you a chainstay length of 425mm and a fork length of 378mm. Now, you have clearance for up to 40mm tires. The taller front end slackens the bike’s geometry by 0.5°, putting the head angle at 72.5° and the seat tube angle at 73° (size large).</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03073457/allied-cycle-works-echos-all-road-gravel-bike-geometry.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03073457/allied-cycle-works-echos-all-road-gravel-bike-geometry.jpg\" alt=\"allied cycle works echo road gravel geometry\" width=\"1200\" height=\"328\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03073457/allied-cycle-works-echos-all-road-gravel-bike-geometry.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/03073457/allied-cycle-works-echos-all-road-gravel-bike-geometry-297x81.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-conte